Instead of a linear relationship, the relationship is exponential where volume increases as a cube of one dimension while strength increases as a square. To elaborate, consider a cube; while the volume inside the cube is the cube (^3) of an edge, its surface area or cross-sectional area is a function of the square (^2) of an edge. Their relationship is not 3:2 as suggested in the video, but rather a cube:square relationship.
